Create project folder:
mkdir DockerWebApp
cd DockerWebApp


Create a simple index.html:
echo "<h1>Hello from Docker Nginx!</h1>" > index.html

Create a Dockerfile:
nano Dockerfile
# Use official nginx image
FROM nginx:latest

# Copy HTML file to nginx default folder
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/

Build the Docker image:
docker build -t mywebapp:1.0 .

Run the container and map ports:
docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name mywebcontainer mywebapp:1.0

Your webpage will be available at:
http://localhost:8080  run this on browser

Confirm it is running: docker ps
Stop the container : docker stop mywebcontainer
Remove the container: docker rm mywebcontainer

